From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:10:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] wlan: build wcnss_service and keep the wlan modules in the
 default namespace

Two changes needed to get WCNSS Wi-Fi/BT up on this AOSP-17 target:

- Build wcnss_service from soong. It is the daemon that opens /dev/wcnss_wlan,
  which is the only thing that drives the kernel's wcnss_node_open() ->
  wcnss_trigger_config() path and sets wcnss_hw_type = WCNSS_PRONTO_HW. Without
  it hw_type stays at the WCNSS_RIVA_HW default and pronto PIL power-up fails
  ("wcnss_core_vregs_on invalid hardware 0" -> "wcnss_wlan_power failed"), so the
  Wi-Fi firmware never loads and BT fails its SoC patch download. The module is
  defined in the sibling Android.mk, but that .mk is unreachable on AOSP-17: the
  top-level Android.mk guards all-subdir-makefiles behind a project-path-for
  check, and project-path-for no longer exists in AOSP-17 build/make, so the
  guard is always false. Soong discovers Android.bp regardless, so define it
  there. TARGET_USES_QCOM_WCNSS_QMI is unset for this target and the QMI code is
  all behind #ifdef WCNSS_QMI, so only libcutils and liblog are needed.

- Drop the soong_namespace declaration. lib_driver_cmd_qcwcn is static-linked by
  external/wpa_supplicant_8's hostapd/wpa_supplicant, which live in the default
  (".") namespace and can therefore only resolve modules in ".". Keeping the wlan
  modules in the default namespace makes lib_driver_cmd_qcwcn and libcld80211
  visible to them, and they stay visible to the vendor namespaces since "." is
  readable from everywhere.
---
 Android.bp               | 10 ++++++++--
 wcnss-service/Android.bp | 34 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 42 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 wcnss-service/Android.bp

diff --git a/Android.bp b/Android.bp
index 9515b25..5da893c 100644
--- a/Android.bp
+++ b/Android.bp
@@ -1,2 +1,8 @@
-soong_namespace {
-}
+// Intentionally NOT a soong_namespace.
+//
+// The wpa_supplicant_8_lib driver-command lib (lib_driver_cmd_qcwcn) is
+// static-linked by external/wpa_supplicant_8 hostapd/wpa_supplicant, which
+// live in the default (".") namespace and can only read ".". Keeping the wlan
+// modules in the default namespace makes lib_driver_cmd_qcwcn / libcld80211
+// visible to those consumers (and still readable by the vendor namespaces,
+// since "." is readable from everywhere).
diff --git a/wcnss-service/Android.bp b/wcnss-service/Android.bp
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..9dc40ad
--- /dev/null
+++ b/wcnss-service/Android.bp
@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@
+// wcnss_service: userspace daemon that opens /dev/wcnss_wlan, which triggers the
+// kernel's wcnss_node_open() -> wcnss_trigger_config() path. That is the ONLY
+// caller that sets penv->wcnss_hw_type = WCNSS_PRONTO_HW (drivers/soc/qcom/wcnss/
+// wcnss_wlan.c). Without it, hw_type stays 0 (WCNSS_RIVA_HW default) and pronto
+// PIL power-up fails with "wcnss_core_vregs_on invalid hardware 0" ->
+// "wcnss_wlan_power failed", so WiFi firmware never loads and BT (shared WCNSS
+// pronto radio) fails SoC patch download.
+//
+// This module is defined in the sibling Android.mk, but that .mk is never reached
+// on AOSP-17: hardware/qcom-caf/wlan/Android.mk gates all-subdir-makefiles behind
+// `ifeq ($(call my-dir),$(call project-path-for,qcom-wlan))`, and the legacy
+// `project-path-for` macro no longer exists in AOSP-17 build/make, so the guard is
+// always false and no kati module under this tree is built. Soong auto-discovers
+// Android.bp regardless of that guard, so we build wcnss_service here.
+//
+// Non-QMI configuration (TARGET_USES_QCOM_WCNSS_QMI is unset for this target): the
+// QMI MAC-address code in wcnss_service.c is all behind #ifdef WCNSS_QMI, so only
+// libcutils (cutils/properties.h) and liblog (cutils/log.h) are needed. The
+// open()-triggered config path is unconditional and does not depend on QMI.
+
+cc_binary {
+    name: "wcnss_service",
+    srcs: ["wcnss_service.c"],
+    shared_libs: [
+        "libcutils",
+        "liblog",
+    ],
+    cflags: [
+        "-Wall",
+        "-Werror",
+        "-Wno-unused-parameter",
+    ],
+    vendor: true,
+}
